### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It handles routing, business logic, reading and writing data from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and rendering HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic will be consolidated here for maintainability and simplicity.

- **data/**  
  Directory containing all the local text files used for data storage as specified in the requirements. These files store books, categories, cart items, orders, order items, reviews, and bestsellers data in the defined pipe-separated format.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the nine pages of the web application. Each file corresponds to one page as per the design requirements:
  - `dashboard.html`: Dashboard page with featured books, bestsellers, and navigation buttons.
  - `catalog.html`: Book catalog with search and category filter.
  - `book_details.html`: Detailed view of a selected book with reviews and add-to-cart button.
  - `cart.html`: Shopping cart page with item management and checkout button.
  - `checkout.html`: Checkout page for entering shipping info and placing orders.
  - `order_history.html`: Displays previous orders with filtering and details.
  - `reviews.html`: Customer reviews listing and navigation to write review.
  - `write_review.html`: Form page to submit a new review.
  - `bestsellers.html`: Displays top-selling books with time period filter.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets such as CSS and JavaScript files:
  - `css/styles.css`: Stylesheet for consistent styling across all pages.
  - `js/scripts.js`: JavaScript for client-side interactivity, such as button actions, filtering, and dynamic content updates.

This structure cleanly separates backend logic, data storage, presentation templates, and static resources, facilitating straightforward development, testing, and maintenance of the 'BookstoreOnline' web application."

